The poem is **Deor** (Old English Elegies, ch. 13). The line naming the smith Welund is the very first line of the poem:

> **Welund him be wurman wræces cunnade,**

"Welund" is the first word — the smith is named right at the opening. The line translates roughly as "Welund knew the worm's misery" / "Welund experienced exile among serpents."
